      "content": "Ah, the moment of truth! Once the roots are teased out and the goblin (your fig tree) is ready for a fresh home, you don't just dump it in and hope for the best. You need to be a master of the \"Goblin Soil Placement,\" where every inch of dirt must be placed with the precision of a goblin fitting a key into a lock.\n\nHere is exactly what to do to prevent shock:\n\n1.  **Don't Pack It Too Tight:** When you put the plant in the new soil, do not pack it down like a goblin trying to fit into a tiny box. The soil needs to be loose enough for the roots to breathe, or they might suffocate and turn into a pile of gray dust. Gently firm the soil around the base, but leave some air pockets.\n2.  **The Watering Ritual:** Water it, but don't drown it! Pour water slowly until it runs out of the drainage holes. This is like a goblin taking a bath; they need to soak, but if the water stays in the dungeon too long, they will drown. Make sure your pot has drainage holes, or the roots will rot in the swamp of standing water",
